  "decisive_point": "The critic’s charge that the forbidden cases are not concrete or possible observations fails on each count. First, the case requiring Linear B and Hittite archives to show stable or declining palace debt relative to stored surplus does not demand that Linear B tablets themselves record compound interest or foreign merchant obligations; it requires that the administrative inventories and the Hittite records, taken together with the broader documentary and archaeological context (seals, Ugaritic and Cypriot commercial correspondence, and storage magazine capacities), show no evidence of rising indebtedness. That is a concrete, verifiable evidential standard routinely used in Bronze Age economic history."
